Hodgkin. Saturday the 27th I paid him six notes, at pretty near four o'clock in the afternoon, a four hundred pound, a three hundred pound, a one hundred pound, a twenty pound, a ten pound, and a fifteen pound; eight hundred and forty-five pound in all. He was intoxicated with liquor. These are the notes; there are the two initial letters of my name upon them; he had five pounds in cash and a spoilt note, that is a cancelled note; that is not negociable; it is made payable only to the person himself; we did not give him a negociable note because he was in liquor. (The spoilt note for eight hundred guineas produced, made out in the name of
Robert Lee
). He brought that note for payment upon the Monday.
